As regards the text, 1 have been content to accept the one recognised by the University, which is that of Baiter and Kayser.

In acknowledging my obligations to former editors I must begin with Mr. J. R. King‚ whose notes in Parker's Series were for a long time the only ones known to me. Long’s Commentary has also been consulted with ad- vantage, and Mr. Donkin’s labours have proved helpful.
